channel.title: FRASER - What's New
channel.description: FRASER® is a project of the Federal Reserve Bank of St. Louis that provides economic information and data to researchers interested in the U.S. economy.
channel.copyright: Copyright 2022 Federal Reserve Bank of St. Louis

item.title: October 2022 issue of the Monthly Labor Review
item.description: Articles include "Traditional Retail in Retreat" and "﻿The Positive Effects of the Measles Vaccine on Long-Term Labor Market Outcomes﻿."﻿

item.title: Economic Indicators, September 2022
item.description: Economic information on gross domestic product, income, employment, production, business activity, prices, money credit, security markets, Federal finance, and international statistics.

item.title: Productivity and Costs News Release, Third Quarter 2022 Preliminary
item.description: Data on nonfarm business sector labor productivity, annual averages for nonfarm business, manufacturing, and nonfinancial corporate sectors from 2019-2021, revised measures, and technical notes.

item.title: Economic Briefs, Nos. 22-42 and 22-43 from the Richmond Fed
item.description: "Trade, Specialization, Property Rights and Wealth Inequality: ﻿A Conference Recap" and "Applied Macro-Econometrics: ﻿A Conference Recap."

item.title: The Mid-Session Review of the Budget of the U.S. Government for Fiscal Year 2023
item.description: The Mid-Session Review contains revised estimates of budget receipts, outlays, and budget authority, and other summary information.
